metadata.abstract: The document 'Sector Splits' provides detailed information on the sector splits for Langen Radar, specifically for RG Frankfurt and RG Düsseldorf within the EDGG FIR. It includes temporary procedure changes for high traffic situations at Frankfurt, noting that RUD and BAD sectors do not cover the Upper with AIRAC 2409. The document is outdated and advises checking actual coverage and priorities using the ATCISS map in unsynced mode. It provides an overview of various sectors, their indicators, frequencies, and callsigns, along with remarks. The document also outlines the complete sectors for Kitzingen, Dinkelsbühl, Gießen, and Baden, including their login details, sector indicators, frequencies, and the areas they cover. It emphasizes that the information is for flight simulator use only and not for real-world flight. The document is authored by Nikolas Görlitz and is associated with vACC Germany.

It includes temporary procedure changes for high traffic situations at Frankfurt, noting that RUD and BAD sectors do not cover the Upper with AIRAC 2409. The document is outdated and advises checking actual coverage and priorities using the ATCISS map in unsynced mode. It provides an overview of various sectors, their indicators, frequencies, and callsigns, along with remarks. The document also outlines the complete sectors for Kitzingen, Dinkelsbühl, Gießen, and Baden, including their login details, sector indicators, frequencies, and the areas they cover. It emphasizes that the information is for flight simulator use only and not for real-world flight. The document is authored by Nikolas Görlitz and is associated with vACC Germany.
